This paper deals with the problem of discovering topical phrases from text corpora, which is a common task in natural language processing and information retrieval. The proposed approach combines a phrase mining framework and a new topic model to discover high-quality topical phrases. This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
